message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Ivory Coast, you have a few transportation options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check for buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. You can ask locals or check with the nearest bus stop for information on the routes and timings.

4. Taxi or Ride-hailing Services: Taxis or ride-hailing services like Uber or Bolt are available in some cities in Ivory Coast. You can book a taxi or use a ride-hailing app to get a ride to the grocery store. This option may be more expensive than others, but it offers convenience and saves time.

Consider the available options, your preferences, and the local conditions to choose the most suitable mode of transportation for your trip to the grocery store.
